    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-24T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-24T21:00:00-05:00" n="320"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Argentina/435: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-24T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 24, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2016. Reference Embassy’s 2547.<note n="40" xml:id="d320fn40">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Supplementing Department’s 2015<note n="41" xml:id="d320fn41">Not
                            printed.</note> in which you have been advised that the United States
                        Commercial Company cannot accept this proposal and that Metals Reserve
                        Company has a contract for and the United States Government an agreement
                        with the Colombian Government for all of that country’s platinum.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The existence of conditions reflected in your telegram would seem to be
                        evidence that some platinum which should go to Metals Reserve is not being
                        obtained by it in spite of the cooperative attitude of the Colombian
                        Government.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>In order that this diversion or smuggling operation in Colombian platinum
                        may be halted, the Department suggests you advise <pb facs="0337" n="325"
                            xml:id="pg_325"/> American Embassy at Bogotá of all the facts relative
                        to this case for such appropriate action as that Embassy may be able to
                        take.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
